http://www.perfect-test.com/index.php/en/technologies-menu-en/technologies-other-menu-eng/38-allure-report-eng

Source : https://github.com/allure-framework/allure-core/tree/master/allure-java-annotations/src/main/java/ru/yandex/qatools/allure/annotations

Summary :
Annotations for test organization : (no need to make weired big name of test methods. we can pass method + parameters in annotation)

@TestCaseId

@Parameter => i preffer Junit parameter over this, but not a bad choice.

@Title

@Description

@Issue => ids of issue tracker

@Issues => hooking multiple issue

@Severity

@Stories

@Features

@Step => the most important usages. We will make all tests reusable with this and make a predefined workflow with group of steps.

parameters =
{method} => takes method name
{0}, {1}, ... => takes all method parameter respectively converted to text


@Attachment
